    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "All 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors have been assessed and each achieves its required gradation level for Model Risk Level 5. Discretisation error (GCI 3.2%) and output comparison (NIH within U95 at all 5 operating points) are the primary credibility drivers at MRL 5 and both meet Gradation 4 requirements. Monte Carlo uncertainty quantification with 1000 samples provides full input-to-output uncertainty propagation. Software quality assurance, independent use-error review, and configuration-managed provenance chain satisfy all procedural requirements. No credibility gaps remain. The CFD model is accepted as fit for purpose to predict absolute hemolysis levels for the Class III VAD device within the defined COU envelope.",
